ZH: 老人家，早上好！
EN: Good morning, old man!

ZH: 不要太紧张，老人家。
EN: Don't be too nervous, old lady.

ZH: 老人家，你今天看起来很精神。
EN: You look very energetic today, old man.

ZH: 老人家，走来走去对身体不好。
EN: Old lady, walking around too much is not good for your health.

ZH: 老人家，你可别忘了吃药。
EN: Don't forget to take your medicine, old man.

ZH: 老人家，别生气，我们只是关心你。
EN: Old lady, don't be mad, we just care about you.

ZH: 她是这个小区里最有名的老人家。
EN: She is the most famous old woman in this neighborhood.

ZH: 老人家在庭院里晒太阳。
EN: The old man is sunbathing in the courtyard.

ZH: 下午茶时间，老人家喜欢喝一杯热茶。
EN: Old lady loves to have a cup of hot tea during tea time.

ZH: 老人家慢慢爬上了楼梯。
EN: The old man slowly climbed up the stairs.

ZH: 老人家的笑容温暖了整个房间。
EN: The old lady's smile warmed up the whole room.

ZH: 老人家的坚强让我们感到钦佩。
EN: The old man's resilience makes us feel admiration.

ZH: 老人家每天早上都在公园散步。
EN: The old lady goes for a walk in the park every morning.

ZH: 老人家一定很想念自己的家乡。
EN: The old man must miss his hometown very much.

ZH: 老人家听到这个消息后很激动。
EN: The old lady was very excited when she heard the news.

ZH: 老人家偶尔会忘记自己放在哪里的眼镜。
EN: The old man sometimes forgets where he put his glasses.

ZH: 老人家喜欢和小孩子聊天。
EN: The old lady enjoys chatting with children.

ZH: 老人家手上有明显的老茧。
EN: The old man's hands have obvious calluses.

ZH: 老人家喜欢晚上看电视节目。
EN: The old lady likes watching TV shows in the evening.
